content: Main Configuration File: Defines project settings, role definitions, and workflow steps.

Manages version control and synchronization with Git repositories.
Agent Orchestration: Core functionality for assigning tasks to dedicated AI agents based on workflows.
A simplified memory structure with fields for Category, Content, and Importance.
Represents a normalized next choice in the workflow, containing display label, next step ID, target step name, and action.
Computes vector embeddings for rapid similarity searches in context management, aiding in memory retrieval and storage.
Abstracts interaction with language models and manages chat requests and prompt construction to facilitate AI agent interactions.
Event-Driven Workflow: Driven by a YAML file allowing dynamic decision branches and predictable flow.
Language: Go - Ideal for performance and concurrency in building scalable services.
Automates task flow and manages decision branches based on YAML configuration.
Autonomous Task Management: AI agents autonomously assign and manage tasks to reduce manual coordination.
Asks the model which memories to delete and updates the context accordingly. It also adds new memories.

Security: Use environment variables for sensitive data instead of hard-coding.
Interface for managing conversation context, allowing operations like remembering, forgetting, setting, and getting context.

Defines basic Git operations for managing a repository, including cloning, writing files, committing changes, and pushing to a remote.
Implements core agent functions and facilitates inter-agent communication for task orchestration and context management.
Modular Design: Each module is self-contained with clear interfaces, minimizing coupling.
Version Control: Store configuration files in Git for tracking changes.
Facilitates real-time communication among agents in a virtual "room".

Dynamic Context Maintenance: Continuous summarization keeps agents updated with the latest project context.

Agent that creates and manages context using documentation and repository information. Initializes with base agent functionality.
Follow Go standards for formatting and maintain clear comments, especially in core modules.
Dynamic Reloading: Allows runtime changes to configuration without redeployment.
Abstracts interaction with language models and manages chat requests and prompt construction.
Notion API: For managing and updating documentation seamlessly.
Implementation of ContextStorage that manages memory in memory (hot and cold storage) with embedding and similarity search capabilities.
Controls the workflow state, managing current steps and generating decision options based on YAML configurations.
Implements operations for storing and managing conversation context using synchronization mechanisms for thread safety.
Embedding Module: Computes vector embeddings for rapid similarity searches in context management.
Maintains a shared context for agents, with memory management through MemoryEntry and EasyMemory.
Target Audience: Agile teams and enterprises seeking to enhance operational efficiency.
